#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:5
msgid "fwctl bnxt driver"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:0
msgid "Author"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:7
msgid "Pavan Chebbi"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:10
msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:12
msgid ""
"BNXT driver makes a fwctl service available through an auxiliary_device. The "
"bnxt_fwctl driver binds to this device and registers itself with the fwctl "
"subsystem."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:16
msgid ""
"The bnxt_fwctl driver is agnostic to the device firmware internals. It uses "
"the Upper Layer Protocol (ULP) conduit provided by bnxt to send HardWare "
"Resource Manager (HWRM) commands to firmware."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:20
msgid ""
"These commands can query or change firmware driven device configurations and "
"read/write registers that are useful for debugging."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:24
msgid "bnxt_fwctl User API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:26
msgid ""
"Each RPC request contains the HWRM input structure in the fwctl_rpc 'in' "
"buffer while 'out' will contain the response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:29
msgid ""
"A typical user application can send a FWCTL_INFO command using ioctl() to "
"discover bnxt_fwctl's RPC capabilities as shown below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:32
msgid "ioctl(fd, FWCTL_INFO, &fwctl_info_msg);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:34
msgid ""
"where fwctl_info_msg (of type struct fwctl_info) describes bnxt_info_msg (of "
"type struct fwctl_info_bnxt). fwctl_info_msg is set up as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:37
msgid ""
"size = sizeof(struct fwctl_info); flags = 0; device_data_len = "
"sizeof(bnxt_info_msg); out_device_data = (__aligned_u64)&bnxt_info_msg;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:42
msgid ""
"The uctx_caps of bnxt_info_msg represents the capabilities as described in "
"fwctl_bnxt_commands of include/uapi/fwctl/bnxt.h"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:45
msgid "The FW RPC itself, FWCTL_RPC can be sent using ioctl() as:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:47
msgid "ioctl(fd, FWCTL_RPC, &fwctl_rpc_msg);"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:49
msgid ""
"where fwctl_rpc_msg (of type struct fwctl_rpc) carries the HWRM command in "
"its 'in' buffer. The HWRM input structures are described in include/linux/"
"bnxt/hsi.h. An example for HWRM_VER_GET is shown below:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:53
msgid ""
"struct hwrm_ver_get_output resp; struct fwctl_rpc fwctl_rpc_msg; struct "
"hwrm_ver_get_input req;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:57
msgid ""
"req.req_type = HWRM_VER_GET; req.hwrm_intf_maj = HWRM_VERSION_MAJOR; req."
"hwrm_intf_min = HWRM_VERSION_MINOR; req.hwrm_intf_upd = HWRM_VERSION_UPDATE; "
"req.cmpl_ring = -1; req.target_id = -1;"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/fwctl/bnxt_fwctl.rst:64
msgid ""
"fwctl_rpc_msg.size = sizeof(struct fwctl_rpc); fwctl_rpc_msg.scope = "
"FWCTL_RPC_DEBUG_READ_ONLY; fwctl_rpc_msg.in_len = sizeof(req); fwctl_rpc_msg."
"out_len = sizeof(resp); fwctl_rpc_msg.in = (__aligned_u64)&req; "
"fwctl_rpc_msg.out = (__aligned_u64)&resp;"
msgstr ""

